<p>Update on what happened across the GNOME project in the week from June 16 to June 23.</p>
<h1 id="gnome-core-apps-and-libraries">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#gnome-core-apps-and-libraries" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>GNOME Core Apps and Libraries
</h1>

<h3 id="text-editor">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#text-editor" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Text Editor <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-text-editor/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Text Editor is a simple text editor that focus on session management.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@hergertme:gnome.org">hergertme</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Text Editor is now using the libadwaita&rsquo;s <code>AdwToolbarView</code>. See <a href="https://blogs.gnome.org/alexm/2023/06/15/rethinking-adaptivity/">https://blogs.gnome.org/alexm/2023/06/15/rethinking-adaptivity/</a> for more information about the new widget and how it can improve adaptability to different form factors.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/d123dc93f3f032356a853156700b39b914e545d1.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="calendar">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#calendar" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Calendar <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>A simple calendar application.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@theevilskeleton:fedora.im">Hari Rana (TheEvilSkeleton)</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p>the &ldquo;Edit Calendar&rdquo; page in GNOME Calendar was recently <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-calendar/-/merge_requests/318">ported</a> to libadwaita widgets! We also added mnemonics to improve keyboard accessibility, as well as tooltips.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/47e91feeed3f79a0efa7889a61fa04126a6f77cf.png" alt="" />


<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/0d3568c615f11617ff765a8474bc0078471df2cf.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@brainblasted:gnome.org">Chris üå±Ô∏è</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p>GNOME Calendar now uses the new AdwNavigationSplitView widget and AdwBreakpoint for adaptivity. This means it now fits properly on mobile portrait mode - something that wasn&rsquo;t possible with the old libadwaita widgets. We also now use AdwMessageDialog instead of GtkMessageDialog.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/5c3fdf7b5bac50879d2d9e37dd92941175bd8b7d.png" alt="" />


<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/ecf8677ec73e31086fdbbce9fb0033c04737c2ca.png" alt="" />


<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/f3711ba684d7532988731ccc33b48d1d4d0e2887.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="web">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#web" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Web <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/epiphany"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Web browser for the GNOME desktop.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@alexm:gnome.org">Alice (she/they)</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Epiphany is using new libadwaita widgets now, as well as AdwTabOverview

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/86ec900a1722230a901d26dd30f8eb728b7f416c.png" alt="" />


<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/88ecac160231bf07a115a9240c4d9738bb92956e.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="disks">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#disks" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Disks
</h3><p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@pothos:matrix.org">kailueke</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>GNOME Disks is in need of contributors for the GTK4 port and the UI refresh planned in <a href="https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-disk-utility/-/issues/274">gnome-disk-utility#274</a> (these mockups have been around for a while). The GTK4 port and the UI refresh could be done separate but it maybe saves work if it&rsquo;s done at once (there could be an easy way to use GTK4 without rewriting the partition view, not sure).</p>
</blockquote>


<h1 id="gnome-circle-apps-and-libraries">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#gnome-circle-apps-and-libraries" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>GNOME Circle Apps and Libraries
</h1>

<h3 id="workbench">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#workbench" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Workbench <a href="https://github.com/sonnyp/Workbench/"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>A sandbox to learn and prototype with GNOME technologies.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@sonny:gnome.org">Sonny</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Workbench 44.2 is out. There are 30 new demos and examples in this release which brings the total amount of Library entries above 50. Each entry is carefully crafted to feature good coding practices, be easy to reason about and respect GNOME HIG and patterns.</p>
<p><!-- raw HTML omitted --><!-- raw HTML omitted --><!-- raw HTML omitted --></p>
<p>Thanks to all contributors, specially Outreachy and GSoC students <a href="https://josecodes.hashnode.dev/introducing-myself">Jos√© Hunter</a>, <a href="https://akshaywarrier.medium.com/gsoc-2023-introductory-post-109019258bd9">Akshay Warrier</a>, <a href="https://sonichere.hashnode.dev/gsoc-2023">Sriyansh Shivam</a> and <a href="https://www.andyholmes.ca">Andy Holmes</a> for co-mentoring.</p>
<p>Here is the list of new entries</p>
<ul>
<li>Popover</li>
<li>Screenshot</li>
<li>Header Bar</li>
<li>Font Dialog</li>
<li>Preferences Window</li>
<li>Web View</li>
<li>Boxed Lists</li>
<li>Drag and Drop</li>
<li>Tab View</li>
<li>Drawing Area</li>
<li>Advanced Buttons</li>
<li>About Window</li>
<li>Animation</li>
<li>TextView</li>
<li>Styling with CSS</li>
<li>Spin Button</li>
<li>Banner</li>
<li>Carousel</li>
<li>Color Picker</li>
<li>Email</li>
<li>Progress Bar</li>
<li>Wallpaper</li>
<li>Drop Down</li>
<li>Video</li>
<li>Revealer</li>
<li>Account</li>
<li>Stack</li>
<li>Status Page</li>
<li>Frame</li>
<li>Account</li>
</ul>
<p>Happy coding!

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/531a9c264d2f9424831f5394e3c6c56d2bfe5576.png" alt="" />


<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/07ad7d7ca581e1dfa3d6cf60effd3a74d62116bc.png" alt="" />


<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/d7785654c4a49629458bd4791f7bb70c08c247c5.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


