<h1 id="shell-extensions">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#shell-extensions" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Shell Extensions
</h1><p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@mnjahn:matrix.org">Marcin Jahn</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I&rsquo;ve developed a new Gnome Shell extension - <a href="https://github.com/marcinjahn/gnome-peek-top-bar-on-fullscreen-extension">Peek Top Bar On Fullscreen</a>. It enables macOS-like capability of revealing Gnome top panel while full screen content is on. Just hover mouse cursor to the top of your primary screen to check the time, or to switch some quick settings toggles, without leaving full screen mode.

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/06/twig-101/tEOsHNpqUxgZBnCvPJShgbdI.png" alt="" />
</p>
</blockquote>


<h1 id="guadec-2023">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#guadec-2023" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>GUADEC 2023
</h1><p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@mwu:gnome.org">mwu</a> reports</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We are getting ready for GUADEC 2023 in Riga, Latvia and we hope to see you there!  Registration is open for both in person and virtual attendance.  Please register early so that we can get an in person and virtual headcount. Why do we ask this? Its helpful to know how popular sessions are, where people are attending from and if there is interest in our events.  To register please go to <a href="https://foundation.gnome.org/2023/05/04/guadec-2023-registration-is-open/">https://foundation.gnome.org/2023/05/04/guadec-2023-registration-is-open/</a>.  We are very grateful for our current sponsors:  RedHat, ARM, Codethink, OpenSUSE, Ubuntu, Centricular, and Endless who have all stepped up in supporting GUADEC 2024. We still need to raise more money and if you or your company are interested, please email <a href="mailto:sponsors@guadec.org">sponsors@guadec.org</a>.  Look fwd to seeing you in Latvia!</p>
</blockquote>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@chenriksen:gnome.org">Caroline Henriksen</a> announces</p>
<blockquote>
<p><a href="https://events.gnome.org/event/101/">GUADEC 2023</a> is only 1 month away! We&rsquo;ve planned two social event options for our final conference day. If you&rsquo;re attending in person in Riga and would like to join us for a <a href="https://events.gnome.org/event/101/page/164-northern-latvia-trip">day trip in Northern Latvia</a> or a <a href="https://events.gnome.org/event/101/page/237-old-riga-walking-tour">walking tour of Old Riga</a>, make sure to register by June 26: <a href="https://discourse.gnome.org/t/join-us-for-guadec-2023-social-events/15764">https://discourse.gnome.org/t/join-us-for-guadec-2023-social-events/15764</a></p>
</blockquote>
